    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.9: \"Electron micrographs of CA1 rat hippocampal sections demonstrating immunogold labeling for GluR3 in asymmetric axospinous synapses.\"\n- Literal: \"CA1 neuropil displayed asymmetric synapses immunoreactive for GluR3, which was localized throughout both the postsynaptic density (PSD) and the synaptic cleft (Fig. 9).\"\n\nNote: \"The specificity of MAb:3B3 for GluR3 in brain tissue sections was demonstrated by preincubating MAb:3B3 with the GluR1, GluR2, and GluR3 fusion proteins. The GluR3 fusion protein entirely blocked the immunoreactivity of MAb:3B3 in cortical sections (Fig. 2; only CA1 shown), while this immunoreactivity was not altered with the GluR1 and GluR2 fusion proteins compared to controls in which the fusion proteins were omitted.\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Electron micrographs of CA1 rat hippocampal sections ...\"",
